<chapter line="1">3. Dvattiṃsākāro</chapter>
<paragraph line="2">Atthi <pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0003" />imasmiṃ kāye –</paragraph>
<gatha1 line="3">Kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco,</gatha1>
<gatha2 line="4">Maṃsaṃ <alternatives line="3"><alternative lang="vri">nhāru</alternative><alternative lang="sī. pī.">nahāru</alternative><alternative lang="syā. kaṃ.">nahārū</alternative></alternatives>  <alternatives line="12"><alternative lang="vri">aṭṭhi</alternative><alternative lang="syā. kaṃ">aṭṭhī</alternative></alternatives> aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ,</gatha2>
<gatha3 line="5">Hadayaṃ yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ,</gatha3>
<gatha2 line="6"><note>( ) sabbattha natthi, aṭṭhakathā ca dvattiṃsasaṅkhyā ca manasi kātabbā</note>,</gatha2>
<gatha3 line="7">Pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo,</gatha3>
<gathalast line="8">Assu vasā kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā <alternatives line="23"><alternative lang="vri">muttanti</alternative><alternative lang="syā.">muttaṃ, matthake matthaluṅganti</alternative></alternatives> .</gathalast>
<centered line="9">Dvattiṃsākāro niṭṭhito.</centered>
